mber":13,"title":"7.6.105","description":null,"creator":{"login":"JeremySkinner","id":90130,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjkwMTMw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/90130?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/JeremySkinner","html_url":"https://github.com/JeremySkinner","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JeremySkinner/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JeremySkinner/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JeremySkinner/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JeremySkinner/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JeremySkinner/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JeremySkinner/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JeremySkinner/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JeremySkinner/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JeremySkinner/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"open_issues":0,"closed_issues":1,"state":"closed","created_at":"2018-08-09T16:58:07Z","updated_at":"2018-10-03T14:41:56Z","due_on":null,"closed_at":"2018-10-03T14:41:56Z"},"comments":2,"created_at":"2018-08-09T16:46:33Z","updated_at":"2018-08-25T14:46:30Z","closed_at":"2018-08-11T14:04:39Z","author_association":"NONE","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"The following Xunit test passes using FV 6.4.1 but fails using FV 7.6.104:\r\n\r\n```csharp\r\npublic class Foo\r\n{\r\n    public string Name { get; set; }\r\n}\r\n\r\n[Fact]\r\npublic void CheckString()\r\n{    \r\n    var validator = new InlineValidator<Foo>()\r\n    {\r\n        v => v.RuleFor(x => x.Name).Equal(\"a\").WithErrorCode(\"nota\"),\r\n        v => v.RuleFor(x => x.Name).Equal(\"b\").WithErrorCode(\"notb\")\r\n    };\r\n\r\n    var foo = new Foo() { Name = \"c\" };\r\n    var result = validator.TestValidate(foo);\r\n    \r\n    result.ShouldHaveError().WithErrorCode(\"nota\");\r\n    result.ShouldHaveError().WithErrorCode(\"notb\");\r\n}\r\n\r\n// Running 1 of 1 tests...\r\n// [FAIL] UserQuery.Bug: Expected an error code of 'nota'. Actual error code was 'notb'\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt looks like the problem is that `ValidationTestExtension.When()` used to have `if (!failures.Any<ValidationFailure>(failurePredicate))`, but now it has:\r\n\r\n```csharp\r\nforeach (ValidationFailure failure in failures)\r\n{\r\n    if (!failurePredicate(failure))\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo it's checking to see if **each** of the validation failures matches, instead of checking to see if **any** of them does.","closed_by":{"login":"JeremySkinner","id":90130,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjkwMTMw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/90130?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/JeremySkinner","html_url":"https://github.com/JeremySkinner","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JeremySkinner/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JeremySkinner/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JeremySkinner/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JeremySkinner/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JeremySkinner/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JeremySkinner/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JeremySkinner/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JeremySkinner/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JeremySkinner/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/FluentValidation/FluentValidation/issues/858/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https:/